Title: Ripple Cuff
Description:
A statement piece guaranteed to start a conversation, the luminous Ripple Cuff evokes the ever-changing texture of water, glistening in polished bronze that catches the light in its organic bends and curves.

With every purchase from the Ripple Collection, 10% of its proceeds will be donated to the great people behind Clean Water Action.

The collection's wavy, luminous texture was designed to symbolize the movement of water — combining metals, various shapes, and finishes. Each piece serves as a daily reminder for its wearer of the effort put toward the continual education and preservation of our most precious life source. We encourage those who wear the Ripple Collection to share the powerful purpose carried within its beauty. For every bit of our history and future relies on a story told, so let this essential one echo far and wide.

Title: You Are Here Necklace
Description:
Each You Are Here concrete pendant slightly differs by shape and its unique texture. The concrete mixture used to slab-form these shapes vary depending on the chosen aggregate added to the cement. The aggregates range from a powdery limestone for a ultra smooth finish to a finely ground sand for a light textured feel and speckled bursts of blue grain. These pieces are coated with a water-based epoxy sealant to protect from moisture and cracking. Then, finished with a clear acrylic spray mist. 

Measurements: 

  • 1" x 1" pendant
  • 24" gold-filled chain

Materials:

  • cement
  • sand
  • limestone

Title: Dance Workshop
Description:
Join an improvisational movement workshop lead by Lily Kane at The Iron Works Factory on Saturday, September 8 from 10-12p. In this class, you will learn more about Lily's choreography process behind Grocery Dance.

Grocery Dance is a durational, site-specific, installation dance piece that premiered at Lucky’s Market in Columbus, Ohio on April 14th, 2017.


Grocery Dance is a public art project that will be performed in grocery stores and supermarkets all over the country, in different demographic locations. 

Grocery Dance is a performance as well as a food drive. A bin is always located at market's exit, encouraging shoppers to donate some groceries to those who can't afford food. After the performance, the grocery dancers deliver the donations to local soup kitchens. 


The 4th installment of Grocery Dance will be hosted by Riverwards Produce Market in Philadelphia, Pa on September 7, 2018 from 1-4p. The performance is TOTALLY FREE!

Title: BROOCH (ONE DAY)
Description:
